Other G40 ICD code text: Lennox-Gastaut syndrome, intractable, without status epilepticus
MRI findings (Chart):
9/6/2016 (EPIC): Gelastic seizures. Hypothalamic hamartoma.The ventricular system is dilated out of proportion to the sulcal and cisternal spaces without evidence of transependymal flow, consistent  with diffuse cerebral volume loss. Leukoencephalomalacia is noted within the parietal and occipital lobes compatible with remote infarction. Signal abnormality is noted within the basal ganglia raising the possibility of remote hypoxic change. The visualized anterior optic pathway is atrophic. This is seen in conjunction with atrophy of the brainstem and cerebellum. There is no evidence of acute infarct, intracranial hemorrhage or intracranial mass effect. The cerebral flow voids at the skull base are patent. The pituitary gland is diminutive in size.

IMPRESSION: Diffuse cerebral volume loss as well as brainstem and cerebellar volume loss. Leukoencephalomalacia involving the parietal and occipital lobes  within the visual cortex seen in conjunction with atrophy of the anterior optic pathway. Chronic hypoxic ischemic change involving the basal ganglia  bilaterally. Small pituitary gland.

The seizures captured are consistent with epileptic spasms associated with high voltage spike and followed by low voltage beta decrement.
